title: Woman dies in Bangor house fire, three others escape blaze - ABC News (Australian Broadcasting Corporation)
text:
Woman dies in Bangor house fire, three others escape blaze Updated February 21, 2017 08:02:43 Map: Bangor 2234 
A woman who died in a house fire in Sydney's south this morning was asleep when the blaze broke out, NSW police have said. 
Dozens of firefighters were called to Paringa Place in Bangor following reports of a large blaze and arrived to find the two-storey house well alight. 
Two occupants managed to escape the inferno but the woman, who was believed to be sleeping on the second floor of the house, was found dead after the fire was contained. 
Superintendent Adam Newberry said the firefighters were unable to enter the house to save the woman. 
"Firefighters worked extremely hard to enter the burning fire to commence the search, however due to the intensity of the fire firefighters had to withdraw," he said. 
The roof of the house has partially collapsed and most of the interior has been destroyed. 
Investigators are trying to determine the cause of the blaze. 
More to come.
